By the Law of Cosines on triangle $OCD,$
\[4 = OC^2 + OD^2 - 2 \cdot OC \cdot OD \cdot \cos (\alpha + \beta) = 2 - 2 \cos (\alpha + \beta).\]By the Law of Cosines on triangle $OFA,$
\[2^2 = OA^2 + OF^2 - 2 \cdot OA \cdot OF \cdot \cos \alpha = 25 - 10 \cos \alpha.\]By the Law of Cosines on triangle $OFE,$
\[3^2 = OF^2 + OE^2 - 2 \cdot OF \cdot OE \cdot \cos \beta = 25 - 15 \cos \beta.\]By the Law of Cosines on triangle $OAB,$
\[1^2 = OA^2 + OB^2 - 2 \cdot OA \cdot OB \cdot \cos \alpha = 25 - 14 \cos \alpha.\]Hence,
\begin{align*}
10 \cos \alpha &= 25 - 1^2 = 24, \\
15 \cos \beta &= 25 - 3^2 = 16, \\
2 - 2 \cos (\alpha + \beta) &= 4.
\end{align*}Then $\cos \alpha = \frac{12}{10} = \frac{6}{5},$ so the answer is $6 + 5 = \boxed{11}.$

